quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  6,9,"And if We had made him [i.e., the messenger] an angel, We would have made him [appear as] a man, and We would have covered them with that in which they cover themselves [i.e., confusion and doubt]."
  6,10,"And already were messengers ridiculed before you, but those who mocked them were enveloped by that which they used to ridicule."